  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Elimelech Moves His Family to Moab'
      title: Elimelech Moves His Family to Moab
      number: 1
      content: '  In the days when the judges ruled in Israel, a severe famine came
        upon the land. So a man from Bethlehem in Judah left his home and went to
        live in the country of Moab, taking his wife and two sons with him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "The man\u2019s name was Elimelech, and his wife was Naomi. Their
        two sons were Mahlon and Kilion. They were Ephrathites from Bethlehem in
        the land of Judah. And when they reached Moab, they settled there.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Then Elimelech died, and Naomi was left with her two sons. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'The two sons married Moabite women. One married a woman named Orpah,
        and the other a woman named Ruth. But about ten years later, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: Naomi and Ruth Return'
      title: Naomi and Ruth Return
      number: 5
      content: 'both Mahlon and Kilion died. This left Naomi alone, without her two
        sons or her husband.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Then Naomi heard in Moab that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> had
        blessed his people in Judah by giving them good crops again. So Naomi and
        her daughters-in-law got ready to leave Moab to return to her homeland. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'With her two daughters-in-law she set out from the place where she
        had been living, and they took the road that would lead them back to Judah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "But on the way, Naomi said to her two daughters-in-law, \u201CGo
        back to your mothers\u2019 homes. And may the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        reward you for your kindness to your husbands and to me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "May the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> bless you with the security of
        another marriage.\u201D Then she kissed them good-bye, and they all broke
        down and wept.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CNo,\u201D they said. \u201CWe want to go with you to your people.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "But Naomi replied, \u201CWhy should you go on with me? Can I still
        give birth to other sons who could grow up to be your husbands? "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "No, my daughters, return to your parents\u2019 homes, for I am too
        old to marry again. And even if it were possible, and I were to get married
        tonight and bear sons, then what? "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Would you wait for them to grow up and refuse to marry someone else?
        No, of course not, my daughters! Things are far more bitter for me than for
        you, because the <smallcaps>Lord </smallcaps>himself has raised his fist
        against me.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And again they wept together, and Orpah kissed her mother-in-law
        good-bye. But Ruth clung tightly to Naomi. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CLook,\u201D Naomi said to her, \u201Cyour sister-in-law has
        gone back to her people and to her gods. You should do the same.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "But Ruth replied, \u201CDon\u2019t ask me to leave you and turn back.
        Wherever you go, I will go; wherever you live, I will live. Your people will
        be my people, and your God will be my God. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Wherever you die, I will die, and there I will be buried. May the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> punish me severely if I allow anything but death
        to separate us!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'When Naomi saw that Ruth was determined to go with her, she said
        nothing more.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "So the two of them continued on their journey. When they came to
        Bethlehem, the entire town was excited by their arrival. \u201CIs it really
        Naomi?\u201D the women asked.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201CDon\u2019t call me Naomi,\u201D she responded. \u201CInstead,
        call me Mara,[[COMMENT(0)]] for the Almighty has made life very bitter for
        me. "
      comments:
      - number: '1:20 '
        content: "<b>Naomi </b>means \u201Cpleasant\u201D; <b>Mara </b>means \u201Cbitter.\u201D"
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "I went away full, but the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has brought
        me home empty. Why call me Naomi when the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has
        caused me to suffer[[COMMENT(0)]] and the Almighty has sent such tragedy
        upon me?\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:21 '
        content: Or <b>has testified against me.</b>
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: So Naomi returned from Moab, accompanied by her daughter-in-law Ruth,
        the young Moabite woman. They arrived in Bethlehem in late spring, at the
        beginning of the barley harvest.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Ruth Works in Boaz\u2019s Field"
      title: "Ruth Works in Boaz\u2019s Field"
      number: 1
      content: "  Now there was a wealthy and influential man in Bethlehem named
        Boaz, who was a relative of Naomi\u2019s husband, Elimelech.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "One day Ruth the Moabite said to Naomi, \u201CLet me go out into
        the harvest fields to pick up the stalks of grain left behind by anyone who
        is kind enough to let me do it.\u201DNaomi replied, \u201CAll right, my daughter,
        go ahead.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'So Ruth went out to gather grain behind the harvesters. And as it
        happened, she found herself working in a field that belonged to Boaz, the
        relative of her father-in-law, Elimelech.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "While she was there, Boaz arrived from Bethlehem and greeted the
        harvesters. \u201CThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> be with you!\u201D he said.\u201CThe
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> bless you!\u201D the harvesters replied.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then Boaz asked his foreman, \u201CWho is that young woman over there?
        Who does she belong to?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And the foreman replied, \u201CShe is the young woman from Moab who
        came back with Naomi. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "She asked me this morning if she could gather grain behind the harvesters.
        She has been hard at work ever since, except for a few minutes\u2019 rest
        in the shelter.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Boaz went over and said to Ruth, \u201CListen, my daughter. Stay
        right here with us when you gather grain; don\u2019t go to any other fields.
        Stay right behind the young women working in my field. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "See which part of the field they are harvesting, and then follow
        them. I have warned the young men not to treat you roughly. And when you
        are thirsty, help yourself to the water they have drawn from the well.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Ruth fell at his feet and thanked him warmly. \u201CWhat have I done
        to deserve such kindness?\u201D she asked. \u201CI am only a foreigner.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CYes, I know,\u201D Boaz replied. \u201CBut I also know about
        everything you have done for your mother-in-law since the death of your husband.
        I have heard how you left your father and mother and your own land to live
        here among complete strangers. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "May the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the God of Israel, under whose
        wings you have come to take refuge, reward you fully for what you have done.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CI hope I continue to please you, sir,\u201D she replied. \u201CYou
        have comforted me by speaking so kindly to me, even though I am not one of
        your workers.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "At mealtime Boaz called to her, \u201CCome over here, and help yourself
        to some food. You can dip your bread in the sour wine.\u201D So she sat with
        his harvesters, and Boaz gave her some roasted grain to eat. She ate all
        she wanted and still had some left over.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "When Ruth went back to work again, Boaz ordered his young men, \u201CLet
        her gather grain right among the sheaves without stopping her. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And pull out some heads of barley from the bundles and drop them
        on purpose for her. Let her pick them up, and don\u2019t give her a hard
        time!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'So Ruth gathered barley there all day, and when she beat out the
        grain that evening, it filled an entire basket.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '2:17 '
        content: Hebrew <b>it was about an ephah </b>[20 quarts or 22 liters].
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'She carried it back into town and showed it to her mother-in-law.
        Ruth also gave her the roasted grain that was left over from her meal.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u201CWhere did you gather all this grain today?\u201D Naomi asked.
        \u201CWhere did you work? May the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> bless the one
        who helped you!\u201DSo Ruth told her mother-in-law about the man in whose
        field she had worked. She said, \u201CThe man I worked with today is named
        Boaz.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201CMay the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> bless him!\u201D Naomi
        told her daughter-in-law. \u201CHe is showing his kindness to us as well
        as to your dead husband.[[COMMENT(0)]] That man is one of our closest relatives,
        one of our family redeemers.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '2:20 '
        content: Hebrew <b>to the living and to the dead.</b>
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Then Ruth[[COMMENT(0)]] said, \u201CWhat\u2019s more, Boaz even told
        me to come back and stay with his harvesters until the entire harvest is
        completed.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '2:21 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Ruth the Moabite.</b>
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u201CGood!\u201D Naomi exclaimed. \u201CDo as he said, my daughter.
        Stay with his young women right through the whole harvest. You might be harassed
        in other fields, but you\u2019ll be safe with him.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "So Ruth worked alongside the women in Boaz\u2019s fields and gathered
        grain with them until the end of the barley harvest. Then she continued working
        with them through the wheat harvest in early summer. And all the while she
        lived with her mother-in-law."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Ruth at the Threshing Floor'
      title: Ruth at the Threshing Floor
      number: 1
      content: "  One day Naomi said to Ruth, \u201CMy daughter, it\u2019s time that
        I found a permanent home for you, so that you will be provided for. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Boaz is a close relative of ours, and he\u2019s been very kind by
        letting you gather grain with his young women. Tonight he will be winnowing
        barley at the threshing floor. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Now do as I tell you\u2014take a bath and put on perfume and dress
        in your nicest clothes. Then go to the threshing floor, but don\u2019t let
        Boaz see you until he has finished eating and drinking. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Be sure to notice where he lies down; then go and uncover his feet
        and lie down there. He will tell you what to do.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CI will do everything you say,\u201D Ruth replied. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'So she went down to the threshing floor that night and followed the
        instructions of her mother-in-law.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'After Boaz had finished eating and drinking and was in good spirits,
        he lay down at the far end of the pile of grain and went to sleep. Then Ruth
        came quietly, uncovered his feet, and lay down. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Around midnight Boaz suddenly woke up and turned over. He was surprised
        to find a woman lying at his feet! '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CWho are you?\u201D he asked.\u201CI am your servant Ruth,\u201D
        she replied. \u201CSpread the corner of your covering over me, for you are
        my family redeemer.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> bless you, my daughter!\u201D
        Boaz exclaimed. \u201CYou are showing even more family loyalty now than you
        did before, for you have not gone after a younger man, whether rich or poor. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Now don\u2019t worry about a thing, my daughter. I will do what is
        necessary, for everyone in town knows you are a virtuous woman. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "But while it\u2019s true that I am one of your family redeemers,
        there is another man who is more closely related to you than I am. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Stay here tonight, and in the morning I will talk to him. If he is
        willing to redeem you, very well. Let him marry you. But if he is not willing,
        then as surely as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> lives, I will redeem you
        myself! Now lie down here until morning.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "So Ruth lay at Boaz\u2019s feet until the morning, but she got up
        before it was light enough for people to recognize each other. For Boaz had
        said, \u201CNo one must know that a woman was here at the threshing floor.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Then Boaz said to her, \u201CBring your cloak and spread it out.\u201D
        He measured six scoops[[COMMENT(0)]] of barley into the cloak and placed
        it on her back. Then he[[COMMENT(1)]] returned to the town.  "
      comments:
      - number: '3:15a '
        content: Hebrew <b>six measures, </b>an unknown quantity.
      - number: '3:15b '
        content: Most Hebrew manuscripts read <b>he; </b>many Hebrew manuscripts,
          Syriac version, and Latin Vulgate read <b>she.</b>
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "When Ruth went back to her mother-in-law, Naomi asked, \u201CWhat
        happened, my daughter?\u201DRuth told Naomi everything Boaz had done for
        her, "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "and she added, \u201CHe gave me these six scoops of barley and said,
        \u2018Don\u2019t go back to your mother-in-law empty-handed.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Then Naomi said to her, \u201CJust be patient, my daughter, until
        we hear what happens. The man won\u2019t rest until he has settled things
        today.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Boaz Marries Ruth'
      title: Boaz Marries Ruth
      number: 1
      content: "  Boaz went to the town gate and took a seat there. Just then the
        family redeemer he had mentioned came by, so Boaz called out to him, \u201CCome
        over here and sit down, friend. I want to talk to you.\u201D So they sat
        down together. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Then Boaz called ten leaders from the town and asked them to sit
        as witnesses. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And Boaz said to the family redeemer, \u201CYou know Naomi, who came
        back from Moab. She is selling the land that belonged to our relative Elimelech. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "I thought I should speak to you about it so that you can redeem it
        if you wish. If you want the land, then buy it here in the presence of these
        witnesses. But if you don\u2019t want it, let me know right away, because
        I am next in line to redeem it after you.\u201DThe man replied, \u201CAll
        right, I\u2019ll redeem it.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then Boaz told him, \u201COf course, your purchase of the land from
        Naomi also requires that you marry Ruth, the Moabite widow. That way she
        can have children who will carry on her husband\u2019s name and keep the
        land in the family.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CThen I can\u2019t redeem it,\u201D the family redeemer replied,
        \u201Cbecause this might endanger my own estate. You redeem the land; I cannot
        do it.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Now in those days it was the custom in Israel for anyone transferring
        a right of purchase to remove his sandal and hand it to the other party.
        This publicly validated the transaction. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "So the other family redeemer drew off his sandal as he said to Boaz,
        \u201CYou buy the land.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then Boaz said to the elders and to the crowd standing around, \u201CYou
        are witnesses that today I have bought from Naomi all the property of Elimelech,
        Kilion, and Mahlon. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And with the land I have acquired Ruth, the Moabite widow of Mahlon,
        to be my wife. This way she can have a son to carry on the family name of
        her dead husband and to inherit the family property here in his hometown.
        You are all witnesses today.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Then the elders and all the people standing in the gate replied,
        \u201CWe are witnesses! May the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> make this woman
        who is coming into your home like Rachel and Leah, from whom all the nation
        of Israel descended! May you prosper in Ephrathah and be famous in Bethlehem. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: The Descendants of Boaz'
      title: The Descendants of Boaz
      number: 12
      content: "And may the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> give you descendants by this
        young woman who will be like those of our ancestor Perez, the son of Tamar
        and Judah.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'So Boaz took Ruth into his home, and she became his wife. When he
        slept with her, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> enabled her to become pregnant,
        and she gave birth to a son. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then the women of the town said to Naomi, \u201CPraise the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        who has now provided a redeemer for your family! May this child be famous
        in Israel. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "May he restore your youth and care for you in your old age. For he
        is the son of your daughter-in-law who loves you and has been better to you
        than seven sons!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Naomi took the baby and cuddled him to her breast. And she cared
        for him as if he were her own. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "The neighbor women said, \u201CNow at last Naomi has a son again!\u201D
        And they named him Obed. He became the father of Jesse and the grandfather
        of David.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'This is the genealogical record of their ancestor Perez:Perez was
        the father of Hezron.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Hezron was the father of Ram.Ram was the father of Amminadab.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Amminadab was the father of Nahshon.Nahshon was the father of Salmon.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '4:20 '
        content: As in some Greek manuscripts (see also 4:21); Hebrew reads <b>Salma.</b>
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Salmon was the father of Boaz.Boaz was the father of Obed.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: Obed was the father of Jesse.Jesse was the father of David.
      comments: []
